HEADWORD: Pettychaps
<hw>Pet"ty*chaps</hw> <pr>(p⟦ecr⟧t"t⟦ycr⟧*ch⟦ocr⟧ps)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any one of several species of small European
singing birds of the subfamily <fam>Sylviin⟦ae⟧</fam>, as the willow
warbler, the chiff-chaff, and the golden warbler (<spn>Sylvia
hortensis</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

